176 #define CANTX_MUX_BOOT_SIGNAL_LENGTH (56u)

179 /** @{
180  * Magic data, i.e., bit muster, in the boot message
181  */
182 #define CANTX_BOOT_MAGIC_DATA_START (0b11111110111111101111111011111110111111101111111011111110uLL)
183 #define CANTX_BOOT_MAGIC_DATA_END (0b00000001000000010000000100000001000000010000000100000001uLL)
184 /** @} */
185 
186 /** @{
187  * Register mapping of 'DIEIDL' (see #CANTX_TransmitMcuWaferInformation)
188  * x-coordinate: bits 0-11 -> 0b_0000_00000_0000_0000_0000_1111_1111_1111 = 0x_0000_0FFF
189  * y-coordinate: bits 12-23 -> 0b_0000_00000_1111_1111_1111_0000_0000_0000 = 0x_00FF_F000
190  * wafer number: bits 24-32 -> 0b_1111_11111_0000_0000_0000_0000_0000_0000 = 0x_FF00_0000
191  *
192  * source : SPNU563A-March 2018: Table 2-47. Die Identification Register, Lower Word (DIEIDL) Field Descriptions
193  * */
194 #define CANTX_WAFER_X_COORDINATE_BITMASK (0x00000FFFuLL)
195 #define CANTX_WAFER_Y_COORDINATE_BITMASK (0x00FFF000uLL)
196 #define CANTX_WAFER_Y_COORDINATE_SHIFT_12_BITS (12uLL)
197 #define CANTX_WAFER_NUMBER_BITMASK (0xFF000000uLL)
198 #define CANTX_WAFER_NUMBER_SHIFT_24_BITS (24uLL)
199 /** @} */

256 static STD_RETURN_TYPE_e CANTX_TransmitBmsVersionInfo(void) {
257  uint8_t data[] = {GEN_REPEAT_U(0u, GEN_STRIP(CAN_MAX_DLC))};
258 
259  /* Set release distance (capped to maximum value) */
260  const uint8_t distanceCapped = (uint8_t)MATH_MinimumOfTwoUint16_t(
261  ver_foxbmsVersionInformation.distanceFromLastRelease, (uint16_t)CANTX_BOOT_MESSAGE_MAXIMUM_RELEASE_DISTANCE);
262  uint8_t releaseDistanceOverflow = 0;
263  if (ver_foxbmsVersionInformation.distanceFromLastRelease > CANTX_BOOT_MESSAGE_MAXIMUM_RELEASE_DISTANCE) {
264  releaseDistanceOverflow = 1;
265  }
266  uint64_t isDirty = 0;
267  if (ver_foxbmsVersionInformation.isDirty == true) {
268  isDirty = 1;
269  }
270  uint64_t underVersionControl = 0;
271  if (ver_foxbmsVersionInformation.underVersionControl == true) {
272  underVersionControl = 1;
273  }
274 
275  uint64_t message = 0;
276  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(
277  &message,
278  CANTX_DEBUG_RESPONSE_MESSAGE_MUX_START_BIT,
279  CANTX_DEBUG_RESPONSE_MESSAGE_MUX_LENGTH,
280  CANTX_DEBUG_RESPONSE_MESSAGE_MUX_VALUE_BMS_SOFTWARE_VERSION_INFO,
281  CAN_BIG_ENDIAN);
282  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(
283  &message,
284  CANTX_MUX_BMS_SOFTWARE_VERSION_INFO_SIGNAL_MAJOR_VERSION_START_BIT,
285  CANTX_MUX_BMS_SOFTWARE_VERSION_INFO_SIGNAL_MAJOR_VERSION_LENGTH,
286  ver_foxbmsVersionInformation.major,
287  CAN_BIG_ENDIAN);
288  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(
289  &message,
290  CANTX_MUX_BMS_SOFTWARE_VERSION_INFO_SIGNAL_MINOR_VERSION_START_BIT,
291  CANTX_MUX_BMS_SOFTWARE_VERSION_INFO_SIGNAL_MINOR_VERSION_LENGTH,
292  ver_foxbmsVersionInformation.minor,
293  CAN_BIG_ENDIAN);
294  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(
295  &message,
296  CANTX_MUX_BMS_SOFTWARE_VERSION_INFO_SIGNAL_PATCH_VERSION_START_BIT,
297  CANTX_MUX_BMS_SOFTWARE_VERSION_INFO_SIGNAL_PATCH_VERSION_LENGTH,
298  ver_foxbmsVersionInformation.patch,
299  CAN_BIG_ENDIAN);
300  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(
301  &message,
302  CANTX_MUX_BMS_SOFTWARE_VERSION_INFO_SIGNAL_RELEASE_DISTANCE_START_BIT,
303  CANTX_MUX_BMS_SOFTWARE_VERSION_INFO_SIGNAL_RELEASE_DISTANCE_LENGTH,
304  distanceCapped,
305  CAN_BIG_ENDIAN);
306  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(
307  &message,
308  CANTX_MUX_BMS_SOFTWARE_VERSION_INFO_SIGNAL_RELEASE_DISTANCE_OVERFLOW_START_BIT,
309  CANTX_MUX_BMS_SOFTWARE_VERSION_INFO_SIGNAL_RELEASE_DISTANCE_OVERFLOW_LENGTH,
310  releaseDistanceOverflow,
311  CAN_BIG_ENDIAN);
312  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(
313  &message,
314  CANTX_MUX_BMS_SOFTWARE_VERSION_INFO_SIGNAL_DIRTY_FLAG_START_BIT,
315  CANTX_MUX_BMS_SOFTWARE_VERSION_INFO_SIGNAL_DIRTY_FLAG_LENGTH,
316  isDirty,
317  CAN_BIG_ENDIAN);
318  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(
319  &message,
320  CANTX_MUX_BMS_SOFTWARE_VERSION_INFO_SIGNAL_UNDER_VERSION_CONTROL_START_BIT,
321  CANTX_MUX_BMS_SOFTWARE_VERSION_INFO_SIGNAL_UNDER_VERSION_CONTROL_LENGTH,
322  underVersionControl,
323  CAN_BIG_ENDIAN);
324  CAN_TxSetCanDataWithMessageData(message, &data[0], CAN_BIG_ENDIAN);
325  STD_RETURN_TYPE_e successfullyQueued =
326  CAN_DataSend(CAN_NODE_DEBUG_MESSAGE, CANTX_DEBUG_RESPONSE_ID, CANTX_DEBUG_IDENTIFIER, &data[0]);
327 
328  return successfullyQueued;
329 }

383 static STD_RETURN_TYPE_e CANTX_TransmitMcuWaferInformation(void) {
384  uint8_t data[] = {GEN_REPEAT_U(0u, GEN_STRIP(CAN_MAX_DLC))};
385 
386  /* Read out device register with die ID low */
387  /* SPNU563A-March 2018: 2.5.1.28 Die Identification Register Lower Word (DIEIDL) */
388  const uint64_t dieIdLow = (uint64_t)systemREG1->DIEIDL;
389 
390  /* see doxygen comment of the macros */
391  uint64_t xWaferCoordinate = dieIdLow & CANTX_WAFER_X_COORDINATE_BITMASK;
392  uint64_t yWaferCoordinate = (dieIdLow & CANTX_WAFER_Y_COORDINATE_BITMASK) >> CANTX_WAFER_Y_COORDINATE_SHIFT_12_BITS;
393  uint64_t waferNumber = (dieIdLow & CANTX_WAFER_NUMBER_BITMASK) >> CANTX_WAFER_NUMBER_SHIFT_24_BITS;
394 
395  uint64_t message = 0;
396  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(
397  &message,
398  CANTX_DEBUG_RESPONSE_MESSAGE_MUX_START_BIT,
399  CANTX_DEBUG_RESPONSE_MESSAGE_MUX_LENGTH,
400  CANTX_DEBUG_RESPONSE_MESSAGE_MUX_VALUE_MCU_WAFER_INFORMATION,
401  CAN_BIG_ENDIAN);
402  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(
403  &message,
404  CANTX_MUX_MCU_WAFER_INFORMATION_SIGNAL_WAFER_NUMBER_START_BIT,
405  CANTX_MUX_MCU_WAFER_INFORMATION_SIGNAL_WAFER_NUMBER_LENGTH,
406  waferNumber,
407  CAN_BIG_ENDIAN);
408  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(
409  &message,
410  CANTX_MUX_MCU_WAFER_INFORMATION_SIGNAL_X_WAFER_COORDINATE_START_BIT,
411  CANTX_MUX_MCU_WAFER_INFORMATION_SIGNAL_X_WAFER_COORDINATE_LENGTH,
412  xWaferCoordinate,
413  CAN_BIG_ENDIAN);
414  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(
415  &message,
416  CANTX_MUX_MCU_WAFER_INFORMATION_SIGNAL_Y_WAFER_COORDINATE_START_BIT,
417  CANTX_MUX_MCU_WAFER_INFORMATION_SIGNAL_Y_WAFER_COORDINATE_LENGTH,
418  yWaferCoordinate,
419  CAN_BIG_ENDIAN);
420  CAN_TxSetCanDataWithMessageData(message, &data[0], CAN_BIG_ENDIAN);
421  STD_RETURN_TYPE_e successfullyQueued =
422  CAN_DataSend(CAN_NODE_DEBUG_MESSAGE, CANTX_DEBUG_RESPONSE_ID, CANTX_DEBUG_IDENTIFIER, &data[0]);
423 
424  return successfullyQueued;
425 }

427 static STD_RETURN_TYPE_e CANTX_TransmitBootMagic(uint64_t messageData) {
428  FAS_ASSERT((messageData == CANTX_BOOT_MAGIC_DATA_START) || (messageData == CANTX_BOOT_MAGIC_DATA_END));
429  uint8_t data[] = {GEN_REPEAT_U(0u, GEN_STRIP(CAN_MAX_DLC))};
430 
431  uint64_t message = 0;
432  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(
433  &message,
434  CANTX_DEBUG_RESPONSE_MESSAGE_MUX_START_BIT,
435  CANTX_DEBUG_RESPONSE_MESSAGE_MUX_LENGTH,
436  CANTX_DEBUG_RESPONSE_MESSAGE_MUX_VALUE_BOOT_INFORMATION,
437  CAN_BIG_ENDIAN);
438  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(
439  &message, CANTX_MUX_BOOT_SIGNAL_START_BIT, CANTX_MUX_BOOT_SIGNAL_LENGTH, messageData, CAN_BIG_ENDIAN);
440  CAN_TxSetCanDataWithMessageData(message, &data[0], CAN_BIG_ENDIAN);
441  STD_RETURN_TYPE_e successfullyQueued =
442  CAN_DataSend(CAN_NODE_DEBUG_MESSAGE, CANTX_DEBUG_RESPONSE_ID, CANTX_DEBUG_IDENTIFIER, &data[0]);
443  return successfullyQueued;
444 }

446 static STD_RETURN_TYPE_e CANTX_TransmitBootMagicStart(void) {
447  return CANTX_TransmitBootMagic(CANTX_BOOT_MAGIC_DATA_START);
448 }

450 static STD_RETURN_TYPE_e CANTX_TransmitBootMagicEnd(void) {
451  return CANTX_TransmitBootMagic(CANTX_BOOT_MAGIC_DATA_END);
452 }

454 static STD_RETURN_TYPE_e CANTX_TransmitRtcTime(void) {
455  uint8_t data[] = {GEN_REPEAT_U(0u, GEN_STRIP(CAN_MAX_DLC))};
456 
457  RTC_TIME_DATA_s currentRtcTime = RTC_GetSystemTimeRtcFormat();

521 /*========== Extern Function Implementations ================================*/
522 extern STD_RETURN_TYPE_e CANTX_DebugResponse(CANTX_DEBUG_RESPONSE_ACTIONS_e action) {
523  STD_RETURN_TYPE_e successfullyQueued = STD_NOT_OK;
524  switch (action) {
525  case CANTX_DEBUG_RESPONSE_TRANSMIT_BMS_VERSION_INFO:
526  successfullyQueued = CANTX_TransmitBmsVersionInfo();
527  break;
528  case CANTX_DEBUG_RESPONSE_TRANSMIT_MCU_UNIQUE_DIE_ID:
529  successfullyQueued = CANTX_TransmitMcuUniqueDieId();
530  break;
531  case CANTX_DEBUG_RESPONSE_TRANSMIT_MCU_LOT_NUMBER:
532  successfullyQueued = CANTX_TransmitMcuLotNumber();
533  break;
534  case CANTX_DEBUG_RESPONSE_TRANSMIT_MCU_WAFER_INFORMATION:
535  successfullyQueued = CANTX_TransmitMcuWaferInformation();
536  break;
537  case CANTX_DEBUG_RESPONSE_TRANSMIT_BOOT_MAGIC_START:
538  successfullyQueued = CANTX_TransmitBootMagicStart();
539  break;
540  case CANTX_DEBUG_RESPONSE_TRANSMIT_BOOT_MAGIC_END:
541  successfullyQueued = CANTX_TransmitBootMagicEnd();
542  break;
543  case CANTX_DEBUG_RESPONSE_TRANSMIT_RTC_TIME:
544  successfullyQueued = CANTX_TransmitRtcTime();
545  break;
546  default:
547  FAS_ASSERT(FAS_TRAP);
548  break; /* LCOV_EXCL_LINE */
549  }
550  return successfullyQueued;
551 }
